.TH TOP(1),User Commands,TOP(1)

.SH NAME
top - continuously display running processes

.SH SYNOPSIS
top

.SH DESCRIPTION
top clears the screen and redraws a table of every running process about once per second, refreshing when the system-clock seconds value changes.

Each refresh shows the current wall-clock time followed by one line per live process.

.SH OUTPUT
Header:

cx16top  HH:MM:SS

Column header:

PID PRI A PAR EXT NAME

PID: process ID in decimal.

PRI: scheduling priority.

A: marked * if the process is the active process, blank otherwise.

PAR: parent PID in decimal.

EXT: number of extended-memory banks owned by the process.

NAME: up to 16 characters of the recorded process name.

.SH KEYS
q, Q: quit.

All other keys are ignored.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: User pressed q.

.SH SEE ALSO
kill(1), ps(1)
